    <s>
      <gd>Aig an ám, cha robh sinn fhéin cinnteach am b’e an t-aineolas no an dànadas a bu mhotha a
        bh’oirrn, oir an uair a thug sinn sùil air ais thar eachdraidh leabhraichean eile de’n
        t-seòrsa, bha ar misneachd corr uair ’gar tréigsinn.</gd>
      <en>At the time, we ourselves were not certain whether it was ignorance or arrogance that was
        bigger on us, because when we looked back across the history of other books of the type, our
        confidence more than once abandoned us.</en>
