  <p>
    <s>
      <gd>Thuige so, chuireadh a mach móran de leabhraichean mall-bhriathrach, oileanach, a bha gu
        ùidh gu leòir do sgoilearan agus do luchd-dreuchd de gach seòrsa; ach tha na tha beò de’n
        Ghàidhlig an diugh, beò air bilean nan daoine cumanta air a’ Ghaidhealtachd—na croitearan
        agus na h-iasgairean agus na mnathan-tighe.</gd>
      <en>Up to now, many verbose, academic books have come out, which were of enough interest to
        scholars and to every kind of professional; but there is that which is alive of Gaelic
        today, alive on the lips of the common people in the Highlands–the crofters and the
        fishermen and the housewives.</en>
